Pre-Covid, AHS was greenlit for up to 13 seasons. As far as I know, it's still on track, so there will be at least 3 more seasons after this one.
I loved the opening, the visuals and cinematography looked like an A24 production

I feel like this entire half of the season is Ryan’s fear of failure and becoming a FAME MONSTER…..SPEAKING OF THE FACT HE DIDNT DO THIS FOR HOTEL WHEN HE HAD GAGA ON BOARD IS A TRAGEDY IN ITSELF. Considering so much of her early work consisted of her obsession with people’s obsession with fame and how it can corrupt ones soul.
